02writeini peak.ini $chan date $date
02msg # New Peak for this channel is $readini(peak.ini,$chan,peak) set on $readini(peak.ini,$chan,date)
02}
02}

12Ovo;;;;;;
from friday 4pm through monday 6am
12Why?
maintenance window for our datacenters
12Argh
and we're the key-management to coordinate all the workings
because we have specialists for Windows-systems, Unix-Systems, Linux-Systems, VMware ESX-Systems, Network, Infrastructure, Comm-networks, Security, Electronics....
and of course: applications
every department needs to be coordinated if their workings affects the others. Like: If you want to patch a Windows System, you need power and access to the memory arrays - and you need to login through the network onto the machine. So you can't take down either network or power or memory banks for mantenance
and our biggest problem: The soccer world cup. Many communication systems need to stay online during that weekend for emergency reaction reasons. That's why we need fallback systems for everything - even whilst we're working at everything

a page's PageRank = 0.15 + 0.85 * (a "share" of the PageRank of every page that links to it)
"share" = the linking page's PageRank divided by the number of outbound links on the page.

I still hate that emote.
(The switches on the mainframe: "HALT" - Stops the computer. Can be fixed with "RUN". "INITIAL PROGRAM LOAD" - Makes the computer reboot... non-fixable. "SINGLE-STEP" - Stops the computer, and causes the operator to have to repeatedly smack "RUN" to make it do anything, can be fixed by unflicking it and hitting "RUN". The power switch - duh. The emergency power switch - even more duh.)
12o3o
Also, the fire-fighting system is applicable to both.
As usually, it will either kill /all/ power to the room and start spraying fire supressant liquid. Or it will start filling the room with Halon. :P
Lol
Since Halon is a gas... it also usually causes a /very loud/ alarm to go off... so not only do you incense every computer user (and cost the place of business several thousand on replacing the gas), you also cause the admins to lose their hearing for a few days. :P
I have no idea how to respond to that except by asking if this is the extent of all the security measures present in the system.

It is also important to note that some runes are "primary," and others are "secondary," this currently is viewabale at the Rune Book, but not in the store. To have a primary rune means that this rune's affect coincides with its type (a mark giving a bonus to attack damage). Secondary runes give a bonus outside its intended use (a glyph giving a bonus to attack damage). Primary runes give a stronger bonus than secondary do (a mark giving bonus to

5The only Mewtwo x OC pairing that has thoroughly intrigued me is the one from Kayasuri-n's Sword & Shield series...
5@Shiny :: Okay, ah...
5OOC is like "Out of Character". It's when someone takes a character from the series, manga, games, whatever and makes them completely different from how they were intentioned to be. It's like a really bad misinterpretation.
:D
5"Canon" is just an original character from the series, manga, whatever. It's established in the franchise.
02All right, I think I understand

turning it on and off and stuff?
You could if you wanted to.
You run a program on your computer, then the DS connects to a specified port, (password protected if you want) and the program basically sends images of what you would see on the computer screen to your DS, which it displays.
You touch the screen to control the mouse.
And use various buttons for other things.
